Business Brief -- Raffoler Ltd.:
   Settlement Is Reached
   With New York State
According to the Attorney General's office, the Long
Island-based company, which does almost $200 million a year
in mail-order business, was the subject of over 3,000
complaints to his office. He charged the company
misrepresented the quality of its merchandise and the value
of sweepstakes prizes offered as sales inducements, and had
kept many customers waiting months for delivery of their
orders. Mr. Abrams added the company used names similar to
well-known trademarks to peddle "cheap imitations."
   An attorney representing Raffoler said the company was
"very pleased" with the settlement and said he felt it
"completely vindicates" the company.